size=1> Just posted on my server msg board, thought I might drop it here as well to get a brouder opinion. Keep in mind Im kinda tipsy atm and most of it is just what popped into my head as I typed, not formatted in any way or order. . .Here goes:<br>
<br>
Can I have a simple answer and your reasoning behind your answer to this.<br>
<br>
&quot;Do you Taunt every time your putton is refreshed?&quot;<br>
<br>
My answer, as with every other person that has any clue of controlling aggro in a group (group, not raid), is a resounding. . .NO<br>
<br>
Numerous Articles have been posted at steel warrior's, many of which I have added statistics and theory's to considering the topic of aggro control.<br>
<br>
I recently had a group in teh planes on a mates war. . .he has pretty decent equip for his level (57). . .BoC etc. First thing that happens while running to the camp is we get jumped by an add. . .no probs, F8 and taunt and start beating the royal @#%$ through it. Between now and the next fifteen seconds the chanted has a slow resist, tashed and slowed. . .and as a consequence of such massive aggro died a rather bloody death. Much to the &quot;WTF?!&quot; coming from my mouth as to why on gods earth someone would be so drastic to slow a yardtrash piece of crap.<br>
<br>
Considering I have played my own and other's high end enchanters, warriors and myriad's of other chars, I now full well the amount og aggro generated by both a war, versus that of a chanter chaincasting their highest hate building spells. Simple answer? No way on gods earth without AeT, bestow DA, or just a simple root, could I have saved the ENC. @#%$ happens.<br>
<br>
Now, something you learn amongst dealing with mobs that deal hundreds of damage per second in melee range, is a quick tip. . .Dont let them get in melee range. Thats why cod chanters get their pets snared, why people ghetto mez, and why I asked the druid to root park the first mob she saw if I said I was pulling 2 or more...<br>
<br>
No problem, root is simple enough, usually sticks without a drama and can allow the enc to easily tash and mez a mob that poses zero thret to him or herself. Why mez a mob in camp when you can mez it outside away from any danger of add's, and far enough that if mez broke the enc could cast another mez by the time it arrived to the group.<br>
<br>
So, this worked well once or twice, amongst my usually hasty group etiquette, of just pulling before the first mob dies (yes, chain pulling, Remember DL, n00bs?)...Great xp if you pull it off...Cudo's to my group as they tried hectically to keep up with the pace which was neither dangerous or boring if people kept their cool's and just remember'd their job and when to do it. Most that group with me know that im about 1 mob short of Sharnhorst style grouping on every pull...But also know the benefits of their dedication and work. (damm fine xp)<br>
<br>
So anyways, the enc, who really I didnt have one problem with as she was doing a good job and mezzing what needed to be mezzed, and only once got the wrong mob. Happens to everyone I guess heh. Well somehow found it amongst my simply request to keep me 'boon'd, and to mez anything that the druid root's, it a duty as to incline why she almost died on several pulls...Because your fu&lt;king tashing and slowing before I get a chance to do even close to an equal amount of hate via taunt and melee damage (BoC proc, yeah right like that ever happens when you need it).<br>
<br>
I tried to explain to her the fundamental's of how verant's aggro system works, which is really quite masterful actually...I tried to explain it all in a story of a group setting and a single mob. . . not to hard to catch the drift on.<br>
<br>
Basically if your curious, there are two definite points in the aggro system. . .Aggro, and nothing...at one point your getting butt raped, and at the other your standing there looking at a fire beetle and admiring the moon.<br>
<br>
The genious abut this system is that the person with aggro, has a definite CAP on the amount of aggro generated above the next highest person. So on and so forth. The cap is in relation to the aggro of the next person down the list.<br>
<br>
As an example, which is used a lot as just a base figour, nothing definite though, of a 1000 point aggro cap between two people, lets call them Ma and Sa. This means that in that given encounter, the Ma can taunt every time it refreshes for the next 5 hours along with doing hundreds of thousands of melee damage, and still remain only 1000 points of aggro ahead of the SA, who just kicked the mob for 1 and went afk.<br>
<br>
Now, considering your aggro a can only be reduced by spells like jolt, degression, khalshazar's defeat, and finally and most commonly, by the person below you ganing aggro points at a higher rate than you. It has brung almost every warrior with half a clue, to the conclusion that repetedly pressing taunt serves no purpose than to delay the gain of 200 aggro (a commonly accepted representation of what a hit of the taunt button generates upon success). . .this means that if I were meleeing a mob like a mother bish, and an enc slow's it (lets say 400 aggro for a resist), tashes (hmm. . .100?), and slows again (600 aggro if it lands [I'm just making these figours up btw]), and I have just depressed taunt I have to wait around 8 seconds before the skill is available, a lot can happen in 8 seconds, and I guarantee you it VERY rarely is a proc of EB, or enough melee damage to get ahead of the enc in the aggro list again. <br>
<br>
Hence, the skill taunt is commonly only used at the begnning of the fight, and then never again (in xp groups, not raids) until such time as the mob dies, or its attention is diverted elsewhere. his means it is available as an extra 200 hate at any time the warrior deems nessesary (when a mobs attention is not solely on him).<br>
<br>
Simple enough no?. . .thought so.<br>
<br>
So, my role in the group was Ma and puller. . .no probs, pulled singles 80% of the time and I would focus by fight with the mob like this..<br>
<br>
Pull with arrow or with proximity if it is in danger of aggroing another mob (yeah remember how we used to do that in sol b guys, think with me, think)...run back to camp in 3rd person makng sure no pops or roamer If so, I'd circle mobs around below camp until one stops moving, which means he is throwing up from running in circles, or more probably rooted by the dr00d.<br>
<br>
Mob would enter camp shortly after me, I'd engage with just BoC and gimpy offhand and taunt at the start as usual, and because I had requested boon, would usually get an EB proc or two within 30 seconds, which would llow me to change to 2hander to take less ripost damage (my group needed nothing but perfect efficiency, so this change of weaps usually from the mobs 80% hp mark down helped a lot according to my parser). Because I had allow'd for two EB proc's along with the substantial melee damage and offhand proc's and initial taunt, I knew I was well ahead of the 2nd person in the aggro list of said mob...<br>
<br>
I knew this, how? because it was hitting me and not him/her, and secondly because I have played well since beta and know the capabilities and aggro generating xpectancies of different classes at different times under different circumstances. Frankly, you just know.<br>
<br>
Now somethng pisses me off when I am blamed for the drds death because a rot broke early. . .There had been a couple of deaths thrugh th group, and nothing that could of been avoided taking into account if people just stayed cool and did their role.<br>
<br>
I was asked where I bought my chards on ebay and for how much no matter how I tried to explain what I did above. You will also obsrve this is a true fact do do with aggro, as it is the predominant reason that a warrior can easily build and take over aggro on a mob with jst an AET ( accepted as 500 hate) and a taunt while ma just doesnt taunt for a tick or two. It is also why it is indescribably easy to outaggro a duel EB war with a mid range 2handed weapon in just a couple of lucky proc's or a few taunts in a row.<br>
<br>
K im getting bored. but main thing is, im sick to death of the kunark express/velks/pop highway to 60+ that leads people through stupendously easy experience for little or no knowledge or game mechanics indulgence for lack of a better word.<br>
<br>
It really is a sad fact, that a the tag of being 65, or 60 is no longer something to respect, but merely just something to idly pass by and wonder how many hours they spent in PoV (/wave meg5 etc, retards).<br>
<br>
Im not in any cicrumstances proclaiming superiority over these people, although in some instances you might call it that, although its just a game. I am merely just bewildered as to how you could go to nearly 60 and not realise some easy and simple facts about aggro. I was questioned as yo why I asked someone to root the mezzed mob etc. . . because I DONT want to sit there mashing taunt 5 times before I break mez, I'd rather have proximity aggro and let my stand alone dps do the job for me, whilst diminishing the mob's hp at the same time. I ask you, would you rather build aggro, or build aggro and kill a mob at the same time? Easy to see what I'd chose.<br>
<br>
Mayb Im just used to a different style of play, where if you let a mob near you it will kill you in 2 rounds. Or maybe its time for some people to stpep back and realise that pulling slingle mobs with 1 minute med breaks and saying please and thankyou after every mez, heal and fart is just bullsh1t when some people put LFG up to join a group, not a fu&lt;king slumber party.<br>
<br>
So I ask you warriors, has 4 years of paying delicate and careful consideration into my actions and their reactions when it comes to game mechanics been totaly flawed by the simple fact that I can destroy all my equip and just click taunt all day and hope for the best.<br>
<br>
To spam taunt, or not to spam taunt, that is the question. My answer is no.<br>
<br>
That is all<br>
<br>
